WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:03.220 --> 00:00:05.860
Are we not the evil ones?

3
00:00:06.670 --> 00:00:11.870
The Shandian warriors...
They attack God's Island, Upper Yard,

4
00:00:11.870 --> 00:00:16.160
only because they wish to reclaim
the homeland of their ancestors.

5
00:00:17.860 --> 00:00:20.360
Are you worrying about
that again, almighty God?

6
00:00:20.360 --> 00:00:23.750
You should look at the blessed
lives of the people of Skypiea.

7
00:00:24.620 --> 00:00:30.550
It's all thanks to our ancestors
securing Upper Yard 400 years ago.

8
00:00:31.060 --> 00:00:34.600
Is it not our duty
to carry on this fight...

9
00:00:34.600 --> 00:00:37.350
and protect that blessing
for this nation?

10
00:00:37.880 --> 00:00:40.450
Surely we've negotiated
as much as possible.

11
00:00:40.450 --> 00:00:44.820
If they remain stubborn, they no 
longer deserve your compassion!

12
00:00:49.690 --> 00:00:52.240
Four hundred years...

13
00:00:53.310 --> 00:01:03.170
The time for either side to accept
defeat may have long passed.

14
00:01:09.170 --> 00:01:11.130
Enemy attack! Enemy attack!

15
00:01:13.010 --> 00:01:14.680
Is it the Shandians?!

16
00:01:14.680 --> 00:01:17.100
N-No, it isn't them…!

17
00:01:17.100 --> 00:01:17.930
What do you mean?!

18
00:01:18.570 --> 00:01:20.390
A man who calls himself God Enel...

19
00:01:21.040 --> 00:01:22.630
God Enel?

20
00:01:40.530 --> 00:01:43.740
Did you know there's an awesome treasure at the end of this sea?!

21
00:01:43.740 --> 00:01:46.540
And whoever gets it becomes King of the Pirates!

22
00:01:46.540 --> 00:01:48.160
Isn't that exciting?!

23
00:01:48.160 --> 00:01:51.210
Cool new adventures are waiting out there!

24
00:01:53.600 --> 00:02:01.260
BON VOYAGE! Hitokakera no yuuki hirogete
BON VOYAGE! Light the ember of courage and let the fire grow

25
00:02:01.260 --> 00:02:08.860
Mirai he no SHIPPO chotto mieta yo
I caught a glimpse at what's beyond the horizon

26
00:02:08.980 --> 00:02:11.410
Back when we first started

27
00:02:08.980 --> 00:02:16.630
Saisho wa minna BARABARA ni egaite ita chiheisen

28
00:02:11.410 --> 00:02:16.630
we had separate ideas about where we would soon go

29
00:02:16.940 --> 00:02:18.580
Things have changed now,

30
00:02:16.940 --> 00:02:23.640
Ima nara hitotsu no bouenkyou de nozokeru

31
00:02:18.580 --> 00:02:23.640
when we look towards our dreams we all share one telescope

32
00:02:23.930 --> 00:02:28.880
When you find that your heart's been led astray

33
00:02:23.930 --> 00:02:33.180
Kimi no KOKORO madowasu unmei no shoppai KONPASU

34
00:02:28.880 --> 00:02:33.180
time to calibrate your compasses

35
00:02:33.180 --> 00:02:36.210
Sakate ni kaji toru yo
Set a new course, turn the tables now

36
00:02:36.210 --> 00:02:43.500
BON VOYAGE! SHIGARAMI mo kako mo sutete
BON VOYAGE! Shed your previous baggage, forget the past

37
00:02:43.500 --> 00:02:50.340
Bokura nara sore demo waraeteru hazu
Smiles can weather a storm, we know that better than anyone

38
00:02:50.340 --> 00:02:52.280
Don't you fret,

39
00:02:50.340 --> 00:02:58.100
Yume wo kanaeru tame no namida naraba

40
00:02:52.280 --> 00:02:58.100
tears shed along the way to your dreams are not in vain

41
00:02:58.100 --> 00:03:04.300
Oshiku wa nai PRECIOUS IN MY LIFE
You know that you're all PRECIOUS IN MY LIFE

42
00:03:05.260 --> 00:03:12.410
Mirai he no SHIPPO chotto mieta yo
I caught a glimpse at what's beyond the horizon

43
00:03:13.300 --> 00:03:18.760
Quintet

44
00:03:19.700 --> 00:03:21.640
Take care of those two, Suu!

45
00:03:22.020 --> 00:03:24.980
I have to go now...!

46
00:03:27.890 --> 00:03:29.680
I'll tell them no matter what!

47
00:03:29.680 --> 00:03:34.280
The islanders will hear the message
you risked your life for!

48
00:03:34.280 --> 00:03:38.030
Now is not... the time for tears...

49
00:03:41.310 --> 00:03:42.330
There!

50
00:03:42.970 --> 00:03:43.880
Ah!

51
00:03:44.660 --> 00:03:46.740
Hey, this house...

52
00:03:46.740 --> 00:03:50.630
You know that pretty lady
who plays the harp on the beach?

53
00:03:51.010 --> 00:03:53.460
Yeah, I know her really well!

54
00:03:53.460 --> 00:03:57.970
Mr. Pagaya and his daughter,
 Miss Conis, live here.

55
00:03:57.970 --> 00:04:00.760
They're both very nice.

56
00:04:01.200 --> 00:04:03.600
One time, they even fed me lunch!

57
00:04:03.600 --> 00:04:07.880
Turns out she's actually
a bad guy! Her dad, too!

58
00:04:07.880 --> 00:04:08.730
What?!

59
00:04:10.080 --> 00:04:11.600
Yeah, I heard about that.

60
00:04:11.600 --> 00:04:14.360
I think they helped bad
people from the Blue Sea.

61
00:04:16.760 --> 00:04:18.030
No way...!

62
00:04:18.030 --> 00:04:21.810
It's true! They're definitely
bad people who went against God.

63
00:04:21.810 --> 00:04:23.030
My father said so, too!

64
00:04:23.360 --> 00:04:26.000
Y-Your father did? I see...

65
00:04:26.400 --> 00:04:29.620
Oh, right, your father is...

66
00:04:29.620 --> 00:04:32.920
Yeah, my father
is part of the Holy Host,

67
00:04:32.920 --> 00:04:34.900
so he's been serving God.

68
00:04:34.900 --> 00:04:38.180
My mother always tells me
that he'll come home soon,

69
00:04:38.180 --> 00:04:40.770
but I don't even know
what he looks like.

70
00:04:40.770 --> 00:04:45.600
He works for God, though!
Your father is super cool!

71
00:04:45.600 --> 00:04:48.790
I hope you'll be able to see him soon.

72
00:04:48.790 --> 00:04:49.850
Yeah!

73
00:04:57.490 --> 00:04:59.860
Skypiea will be dropped
to the Blue Sea!

74
00:05:00.260 --> 00:05:01.990
This nation will disappear!

75
00:05:04.740 --> 00:05:07.740
I can't let that man's
sacrifice be for nothing!

76
00:05:07.740 --> 00:05:10.410
I have to tell them… No matter what!

77
00:05:15.290 --> 00:05:16.630
Ruins?

78
00:05:17.200 --> 00:05:21.090
Why have so many
pieces fallen from above?

79
00:05:24.380 --> 00:05:25.750
Swordsman!

80
00:05:25.750 --> 00:05:27.280
This is not my day...

81
00:05:27.280 --> 00:05:29.850
Don't tell me you fell with the ruins...

82
00:05:30.920 --> 00:05:34.400
Dammit! I could've died!

83
00:05:34.400 --> 00:05:35.900
Yeah, that's what happens...

84
00:05:35.900 --> 00:05:37.530
to normal people.

85
00:05:37.980 --> 00:05:39.890
Oh, it's you.

86
00:05:39.890 --> 00:05:41.490
Where the heck are we?

87
00:05:41.970 --> 00:05:44.660
This is the City of Gold
you've been looking for.

88
00:05:44.660 --> 00:05:46.870
So, did you find the treasure?

89
00:05:46.870 --> 00:05:50.160
No, there was no gold here.

90
00:06:16.210 --> 00:06:20.210
Whew... This giant snake
is really something else, huh?

91
00:06:20.210 --> 00:06:21.820
We're back where we started!

92
00:06:22.130 --> 00:06:26.610
Are you stupid?! Why would you
hold onto the waver's jet?!

93
00:06:27.490 --> 00:06:28.470
My bad.

94
00:06:28.470 --> 00:06:30.300
Everyone else made it outside!

95
00:06:30.300 --> 00:06:33.930
We've been left behind!
It's all your fault!

96
00:06:33.930 --> 00:06:35.110
Don't worry!

97
00:06:35.110 --> 00:06:35.920
What now?

98
00:06:36.220 --> 00:06:41.120
Well, how about we head over
to its butthole and pop out there?

99
00:06:41.120 --> 00:06:43.050
How about no, thank you!

100
00:06:47.790 --> 00:06:48.810
Oh, it's the horse!

101
00:06:48.810 --> 00:06:50.200
That's a bird!

102
00:06:53.110 --> 00:06:54.980
Ow, ow, ow...

103
00:06:55.300 --> 00:06:57.440
Thanks, weird knight!

104
00:06:59.420 --> 00:07:02.690
We were fortunate
to have landed on these clouds.

105
00:07:03.160 --> 00:07:06.740
Luffy and Aisa are still in there,
though. I hope they're alright.

106
00:07:06.990 --> 00:07:13.460
Fear not. When push comes to shove,
Pierre is quite the reliable bird or horse.

107
00:07:13.460 --> 00:07:16.400
Hey, where are we, anyway?

108
00:07:16.400 --> 00:07:19.280
In terms of location,
we're likely underground...

109
00:07:19.280 --> 00:07:23.380
though I confess, I do not recognize
this place. Where could we be...?

110
00:07:24.710 --> 00:07:25.510
Thanks.

111
00:07:28.360 --> 00:07:33.490
To think all this time a place
like this existed in Upper Yard…

112
00:07:39.150 --> 00:07:41.860
Is it possible... that this place...

113
00:07:46.710 --> 00:07:51.240
is the homeland of the Shandians?!

114
00:08:06.650 --> 00:08:09.110
– Shine the Light of Shandora!
– Shine the Light of Shandora!

115
00:08:10.360 --> 00:08:13.100
– In the name of the great warrior Kalgara!
– In the name of the great warrior Kalgara!

116
00:08:13.870 --> 00:08:15.930
– Shine the Light of Shandora!
– Shine the Light of Shandora!

117
00:08:19.690 --> 00:08:21.380
– We're going back!
– We're going back!

118
00:08:21.380 --> 00:08:23.150
– To our homeland!
– To our homeland!

119
00:08:23.950 --> 00:08:25.700
– To our homeland!
– To our homeland!

120
00:08:28.240 --> 00:08:32.080
This is it... We've finally made it!

121
00:08:32.080 --> 00:08:35.330
The proud city that
our ancestors protected!

122
00:08:36.350 --> 00:08:37.680
Shandora!

123
00:08:49.770 --> 00:08:52.880
That snake looks like
it's searching for something…

124
00:08:52.880 --> 00:08:55.560
or maybe Luffy is
up to something again?

125
00:09:02.380 --> 00:09:04.190
Either way, it's acting strange.

126
00:09:10.260 --> 00:09:11.320
It's crying!

127
00:09:14.330 --> 00:09:17.740
What's the meaning of this,
Master of the Sky?

128
00:09:17.740 --> 00:09:19.650
Why are you so worked up?

129
00:09:21.480 --> 00:09:23.630
You irksome snake!

130
00:09:25.960 --> 00:09:27.390
Mindless beast!

131
00:09:28.590 --> 00:09:29.920
El Thor!

132
00:09:33.390 --> 00:09:34.800
Aisa!

133
00:09:34.800 --> 00:09:36.800
Crap! Nami!

134
00:09:36.800 --> 00:09:39.230
She can't survive that!

135
00:09:40.530 --> 00:09:44.130
Oh? Zoro! Robin, too!

136
00:09:44.130 --> 00:09:45.460
You were right there?!

137
00:09:45.460 --> 00:09:47.720
When did you get out of 
that snake's stomach?!

138
00:09:47.720 --> 00:09:50.150
Why are you here, Miss Navigator?

139
00:09:50.640 --> 00:09:53.280
Well, I'm fine...

140
00:09:53.280 --> 00:09:55.870
But Luffy's still...

141
00:09:56.960 --> 00:09:58.490
inside the snake.

142
00:09:58.490 --> 00:10:01.390
Huh? Why in the world is he...?!

143
00:10:01.390 --> 00:10:03.830
It's not my fault; I found him in there!

144
00:10:04.300 --> 00:10:08.450
Come on...! Why is he always
such a pain in the ass?!

145
00:10:08.450 --> 00:10:09.300
You tell me!

146
00:10:13.490 --> 00:10:14.800
Just one hit…

147
00:10:15.180 --> 00:10:17.410
Even though the bazooka...

148
00:10:17.410 --> 00:10:20.140
barely scratched
the Master of the Sky.

149
00:10:20.480 --> 00:10:23.350
Dammit! Aisa could be hurt!

150
00:10:32.260 --> 00:10:33.540
Ball Cloud!

151
00:10:34.910 --> 00:10:36.450
Enel!

152
00:10:39.270 --> 00:10:40.700
What was that for?

153
00:10:40.700 --> 00:10:44.920
That wasn't very courteous of you, 
Wyper the warrior.

154
00:10:45.770 --> 00:10:50.030
After all, I graciously invited you
here to your homeland.

155
00:10:50.700 --> 00:10:54.180
There will be a time for that.
Save your anger.

156
00:10:54.750 --> 00:10:58.550
The game isn't over yet.

157
00:10:58.940 --> 00:11:00.260
This is a game to you?!

158
00:11:00.650 --> 00:11:03.980
That's right. A silly little game.

159
00:11:03.980 --> 00:11:08.610
With you... and the other
contestants right behind you.

160
00:11:20.960 --> 00:11:24.730
Welcome, eager survivors!

161
00:11:24.730 --> 00:11:29.060
Congratulations on getting this far.
You have earned my praise.

162
00:11:35.550 --> 00:11:38.700
What's wrong?
I'm only having a little fun.

163
00:11:38.700 --> 00:11:43.120
This is a survival game to see
how many people out of eighty-one

164
00:11:43.120 --> 00:11:49.420
will be left standing three hours
after your arrival to the island.

165
00:11:50.160 --> 00:11:52.680
Myself included, of course.

166
00:11:53.350 --> 00:11:55.810
Some participants entered afterward,

167
00:11:55.810 --> 00:11:57.950
but I've decided to allow it.

168
00:11:59.350 --> 00:12:02.530
I predicted that there
would be five survivors.

169
00:12:04.730 --> 00:12:06.280
Did he say five?!

170
00:12:06.280 --> 00:12:11.030
Zoro, Robin, the weird knight,
bazooka man, and Enel.

171
00:12:11.030 --> 00:12:13.300
That's exactly five people, right?

172
00:12:14.650 --> 00:12:16.930
Good, so he hasn't noticed me.

173
00:12:16.930 --> 00:12:20.260
In three minutes,
three hours will have passed.

174
00:12:21.220 --> 00:12:26.230
Therefore, it won't do if
there are six people still standing.

175
00:12:26.530 --> 00:12:28.640
Crap! He knows!

176
00:12:28.980 --> 00:12:34.610
God's prophecy cannot fail,
since he is absolute.

177
00:12:35.310 --> 00:12:40.920
So, who will be the one to fall?
Will you eliminate one another?

178
00:12:42.910 --> 00:12:47.080
Or shall I see to it myself?

179
00:12:51.670 --> 00:12:53.200
You wanna be the one?

180
00:12:53.200 --> 00:12:54.870
I'd rather not.

181
00:12:54.870 --> 00:12:55.880
Me neither.

182
00:12:56.320 --> 00:12:57.970
It won't be me.

183
00:12:58.820 --> 00:13:01.090
I, too, firmly refuse.

184
00:13:04.430 --> 00:13:06.850
Hey, hold on a sec! I–

185
00:13:12.350 --> 00:13:14.400
So that leaves you!

186
00:13:22.280 --> 00:13:23.920
How insolent.

187
00:13:24.910 --> 00:13:27.340
You're telling me to die?

188
00:13:32.290 --> 00:13:35.040
This can't end well... He's dangerous!

189
00:13:37.790 --> 00:13:40.260
I'd want nothing less
from the game's survivors.

190
00:13:40.570 --> 00:13:47.090
However... you have yet
to realize who you're talking to.

191
00:13:51.110 --> 00:13:57.150
It seems you have yet to grasp
what being a god truly means.

192
00:14:01.380 --> 00:14:04.530
An old fool wishing
for Skypiea's happiness…

193
00:14:04.980 --> 00:14:07.910
A warrior single-mindedly
desiring his homeland…

194
00:14:08.320 --> 00:14:12.290
And thieves from
the Blue Sea seeking gold…

195
00:14:12.800 --> 00:14:14.930
In this world full of anguish,

196
00:14:14.930 --> 00:14:18.250
I don't concern myself
with the wishes of my flock…

197
00:14:18.610 --> 00:14:21.880
for something is fundamentally
wrong with this nation.

198
00:14:23.610 --> 00:14:26.240
If you have time
to spout such nonsense,

199
00:14:26.240 --> 00:14:28.390
tell me where the Holy Host is!

200
00:14:30.910 --> 00:14:33.140
Just what is your goal?!

201
00:14:33.710 --> 00:14:36.810
The return of the divine, Gan Fall.

202
00:14:37.090 --> 00:14:38.440
"The return of the divine"?

203
00:14:38.680 --> 00:14:44.000
Indeed. After completing a visit, 
a god must return to his rightful place.

204
00:14:45.160 --> 00:14:48.620
Return? Are you planning 
to leave Skypiea?

205
00:14:49.460 --> 00:14:53.380
That's right. I'm needed elsewhere.

206
00:14:53.380 --> 00:14:58.590
According to my sky island's teachings,
it is the realm of the almighty.

207
00:14:58.880 --> 00:15:00.130
Where is that...?

208
00:15:00.650 --> 00:15:03.940
It is known as the Endless Vearth.

209
00:15:03.940 --> 00:15:09.640
There, the ground extends
as far as the eye can see!

210
00:15:09.640 --> 00:15:13.100
That is precisely
the dream world that I seek!

211
00:15:15.560 --> 00:15:19.400
This Endless Vearth
is perfect for God!

212
00:15:20.480 --> 00:15:27.720
Fighting over Upper Yard—such
small vearth—is a petty triviality.

213
00:15:31.210 --> 00:15:36.570
Hear me. The root of your
conflicts lies in a deeper place.

214
00:15:37.640 --> 00:15:39.480
Think about it.

215
00:15:41.460 --> 00:15:43.840
You were born in the sky,
yet you're not a cloud.

216
00:15:43.840 --> 00:15:46.760
You live in the sky,
yet you're not a bird.

217
00:15:48.620 --> 00:15:51.440
This very nation, rooted in the sky…

218
00:15:51.440 --> 00:15:54.320
is a fundamentally
unnatural existence.

219
00:15:54.320 --> 00:16:00.310
Land, people, even gods...
They all have a place to return to.

220
00:16:01.280 --> 00:16:03.320
D-Don't tell me, you…

221
00:16:06.300 --> 00:16:09.280
It's nothing you should
be surprised about.

222
00:16:09.560 --> 00:16:16.080
You see, even an almighty god...
must adhere to the laws of nature.

223
00:16:17.560 --> 00:16:22.920
So, yes! I will drag every human back down
to their rightful place: beneath the sky!

224
00:16:28.770 --> 00:16:31.430
Are you planning to destroy
the entire nation...?!

225
00:16:32.400 --> 00:16:34.220
It's only natural.

226
00:16:37.560 --> 00:16:39.150
How arrogant, Enel!

227
00:16:39.150 --> 00:16:42.610
"God" is just the title for
leader here! Nothing more!

228
00:16:43.110 --> 00:16:45.570
Yes, up until now, anyway.

229
00:16:48.070 --> 00:16:51.910
Gods do not exist in the human world!

230
00:16:54.330 --> 00:16:57.350
Former god, Gan Fall...

231
00:16:59.580 --> 00:17:03.120
If I recall correctly, weren't you
worried about the Holy Host?

232
00:17:07.040 --> 00:17:13.810
It's been 6 years since I defeated you
and claimed your 650 followers.

233
00:17:16.420 --> 00:17:22.230
Just this morning, they completed the work
I requested, right here on this island.

234
00:17:23.570 --> 00:17:25.080
I told you, didn't I?

235
00:17:25.080 --> 00:17:28.940
There are only six people
standing on this island right now.

236
00:17:29.330 --> 00:17:30.870
What a shame...

237
00:17:30.870 --> 00:17:32.910
Y-You...

238
00:17:34.070 --> 00:17:37.120
It's not that I wanted to harm them.

239
00:17:37.120 --> 00:17:40.540
When I told them my next goal...

240
00:17:42.590 --> 00:17:45.630
they charged at me,
faces twisted in fury!

241
00:17:48.990 --> 00:17:52.210
Those people all have
family on Angel Island!

242
00:17:52.210 --> 00:17:56.430
Yes, I know. I suppose I'll have
to bury their families soon, too.

243
00:17:59.650 --> 00:18:01.440
Are you...

244
00:18:06.970 --> 00:18:12.050
evil incarnate?!

245
00:18:24.260 --> 00:18:25.600
Five Million...

246
00:18:25.600 --> 00:18:27.130
Ten Million...

247
00:18:27.130 --> 00:18:28.630
Twenty Million...!

248
00:18:34.940 --> 00:18:39.890
Almighty Enel, what shall we do
with the newly fallen god?

249
00:18:39.890 --> 00:18:42.790
Just throw him in the sea
or something.

250
00:18:42.790 --> 00:18:44.850
He can't even be
used for manual labor.

251
00:18:46.500 --> 00:18:49.610
I must say, this is quite a nice shrine.

252
00:18:49.610 --> 00:18:52.530
But what we need is the Holy Host.

253
00:18:53.070 --> 00:18:58.370
My new followers will be
working very hard.

254
00:18:58.370 --> 00:19:00.950
My followers…

255
00:19:01.710 --> 00:19:05.460
Silence! You are a god no longer!

256
00:19:13.620 --> 00:19:15.630
20 Million Volts...

257
00:19:17.090 --> 00:19:18.470
Vari!

258
00:19:20.960 --> 00:19:22.020
Weird knight!

259
00:19:22.020 --> 00:19:23.140
Old man!

260
00:19:26.660 --> 00:19:28.480
God exists in this world.

261
00:19:28.730 --> 00:19:30.620
How mortifying...!

262
00:19:31.140 --> 00:19:33.610
That god... is me!

263
00:19:40.410 --> 00:19:41.370
A devil fruit?!

264
00:19:41.890 --> 00:19:43.450
Must be the Thunder-Thunder Fruit...!

265
00:19:43.900 --> 00:19:46.700
If I'm not mistaken,
among the many kinds of powers,

266
00:19:46.700 --> 00:19:48.990
it's one of the few
considered invincible.

267
00:19:50.820 --> 00:19:52.320
The power of lightning!

268
00:19:55.760 --> 00:20:00.760
Lightning... No human
could stand up to that!

269
00:20:04.150 --> 00:20:07.750
Well now, the prophesied time is here.

270
00:20:07.750 --> 00:20:08.520
And thus...

271
00:20:11.250 --> 00:20:15.190
there are five!
Well done on surviving!

272
00:20:17.680 --> 00:20:20.620
Now, I shall bring you along with me!

273
00:20:20.620 --> 00:20:23.490
To the dream world
I am departing for!

274
00:20:24.520 --> 00:20:29.670
To the Endless Vearth!
You will join me there!

275
00:20:30.750 --> 00:20:31.750
What?

276
00:20:31.750 --> 00:20:37.140
There, I shall build
a truly glorious God Land!

277
00:20:37.140 --> 00:20:40.600
We, the chosen people,
will be its only inhabitants.

278
00:20:42.190 --> 00:20:44.100
What is that guy talking about?

279
00:20:44.530 --> 00:20:49.100
If my followers cannot
handle this measly survival game,

280
00:20:49.810 --> 00:20:54.070
then their presence would only
lower my nation's stature.

281
00:20:55.930 --> 00:20:59.950
And... what if we refuse?

282
00:21:00.830 --> 00:21:01.670
Robin!

283
00:21:01.670 --> 00:21:02.820
Refuse?

284
00:21:03.240 --> 00:21:05.790
Why? It was decided by God.

285
00:21:06.130 --> 00:21:10.420
If you stay here, you'll fall into
the abyss with this nation.

286
00:21:10.760 --> 00:21:15.280
I won't deny you would be
able to perform such a feat.

287
00:21:15.280 --> 00:21:17.800
But if you carelessly
destroy this nation,

288
00:21:17.800 --> 00:21:22.050
the object you desire
will fall with it, yes?

289
00:21:22.770 --> 00:21:24.390
You mean the golden bell?!

290
00:21:24.710 --> 00:21:25.810
That's right.

291
00:21:26.080 --> 00:21:27.520
Golden bell...?

292
00:21:28.680 --> 00:21:30.330
The golden bell...

293
00:21:32.310 --> 00:21:36.780
You needn't worry.
I know where to start looking.

294
00:21:37.280 --> 00:21:42.610
Recalling the actions you took
leads to but one conclusion.

295
00:21:44.280 --> 00:21:48.950
I believe we're both
thinking of the same place.

296
00:21:49.420 --> 00:21:51.290
You seem surprised.

297
00:21:52.200 --> 00:21:57.250
Did you think you'd be able to
outwit me by mentioning that?

298
00:21:58.080 --> 00:22:00.020
How foolish...

299
00:22:01.220 --> 00:22:02.340
Robin!

300
00:22:02.840 --> 00:22:05.930
I hate conniving women.

301
00:22:14.070 --> 00:22:15.270
No...

302
00:22:32.730 --> 00:22:33.920
She's a woman!

303
00:22:35.790 --> 00:22:37.130
I can see that.

304
00:22:52.980 --> 00:22:54.230
You're quite skilled.

305
00:22:54.760 --> 00:22:56.980
Are you out of your mind?!

306
00:23:06.990 --> 00:23:08.990
Burn Bazooka!

307
00:23:13.160 --> 00:23:14.280
Kari!

308
00:23:24.670 --> 00:23:28.300
I-It can't be! He neutralized
the bazooka's blast!

309
00:23:29.910 --> 00:23:32.560
You still don't get it, do you?

310
00:23:32.560 --> 00:23:37.770
The energy you wield
is pitiful compared to mine.

311
00:23:38.310 --> 00:23:40.690
The thunder reverberated...

312
00:23:40.690 --> 00:23:43.610
which means the air expanded
at the speed of sound!

313
00:23:43.610 --> 00:23:44.900
That's insane power!

314
00:23:45.270 --> 00:23:48.270
None of us can even come close!

315
00:23:48.720 --> 00:23:52.370
H-He really is... lightning itself!

316
00:23:52.800 --> 00:23:59.640
My goodness… We're about to
set off together to the Endless Vearth.

317
00:24:00.350 --> 00:24:02.500
There's no need
to get so bloodthirsty.

318
00:24:03.810 --> 00:24:06.300
Who said we're coming with you?

319
00:24:11.060 --> 00:24:15.180
I don't care about this
so-called dream world of yours!

320
00:24:16.280 --> 00:24:19.350
Stop, Zoro! Don't fight him!
You can't win this!

321
00:24:19.930 --> 00:24:22.610
It seems your body
will have to be taught…

322
00:24:23.420 --> 00:24:24.990
the meaning of god.

323
00:24:39.710 --> 00:24:42.000
God's overwhelming power
cannot be matched,

324
00:24:42.000 --> 00:24:45.170
no matter how hard you struggle!

325
00:24:45.520 --> 00:24:47.760
That's when you feel it…

326
00:24:48.520 --> 00:24:50.090
The despair!

327
00:24:55.750 --> 00:25:00.440
Having all your hopes crushed
is the same as death itself.

328
00:25:05.790 --> 00:25:06.610
Zoro!

329
00:25:07.280 --> 00:25:10.700
People fear death above all things!

330
00:25:13.880 --> 00:25:18.650
That's why people prostrate themselves
before gods and beg for mercy.

331
00:25:18.650 --> 00:25:20.560
It simply can't be helped.

332
00:25:20.560 --> 00:25:24.130
Living beings are made to kneel
before that which they fear.

333
00:25:24.130 --> 00:25:27.590
What a pity… It's just instinct.

334
00:25:27.590 --> 00:25:31.090
What's with this guy...?
He's incredibly strong!

335
00:25:38.440 --> 00:25:39.680
What's this, now?

336
00:25:42.460 --> 00:25:44.860
Have you come to perish?

337
00:25:45.300 --> 00:25:45.690
What the...?!

338
00:25:46.030 --> 00:25:49.190
Are you familiar with seastone, Enel?!

339
00:25:50.820 --> 00:25:52.720
Seastone?

340
00:25:52.720 --> 00:25:55.450
Doesn't that stuff nullify devil fruits?!

341
00:26:01.750 --> 00:26:04.550
I see... I feel weakened.

342
00:26:06.040 --> 00:26:11.670
Seastone... That stuff radiates
the same energy as the sea.

343
00:26:11.670 --> 00:26:14.650
It's basically the sea in solid form.

344
00:26:14.650 --> 00:26:18.010
That's why it can weaken
the power of devil fruits!

345
00:26:18.320 --> 00:26:20.420
Go to hell!

346
00:26:20.420 --> 00:26:24.350
Y-You shouldn't... You're going
to use a reject dial, right?

347
00:26:24.710 --> 00:26:27.790
Your body will pay
a heavy price as well!

348
00:26:27.790 --> 00:26:30.860
What frustrates you now?
You also desire vearth, do you not?

349
00:26:31.100 --> 00:26:34.700
Shut up! I'm happy to die...

350
00:26:35.150 --> 00:26:38.360
if I can take you with me!

351
00:26:38.360 --> 00:26:40.400
S-Stop!

352
00:26:43.790 --> 00:26:45.040
Reject!

353
00:26:50.200 --> 00:26:53.340
Hold the truth in your heart,
and speak not of it.

354
00:26:53.340 --> 00:26:56.340
We are the ones who weave history.

355
00:26:56.340 --> 00:27:01.420
Those were the words inscribed
on a poneglyph 800 years ago.

356
00:27:03.160 --> 00:27:04.630
Poneglyph?

357
00:27:08.160 --> 00:27:11.280
When those who sought
the stone invaded,

358
00:27:11.280 --> 00:27:15.450
the warriors of Shandora,
the City of Gold, fought bravely.

359
00:27:16.350 --> 00:27:17.440
Did they win?

360
00:27:17.940 --> 00:27:20.000
Yes, they won.

361
00:27:20.730 --> 00:27:26.370
However, the fierce battle took
a great toll on our warriors.

362
00:27:26.900 --> 00:27:30.460
The few who survived became guards

363
00:27:30.460 --> 00:27:36.000
and solemnly watched over
the ruined city and the poneglyph.

364
00:27:37.320 --> 00:27:41.060
And we're their direct descendants?

365
00:27:41.570 --> 00:27:46.570
But the island flew up
to Skypiea 400 years ago.

366
00:27:46.570 --> 00:27:49.040
And it was taken by Skypieans.

367
00:27:49.840 --> 00:27:52.800
Our ancestors tried so hard
to protect our land.

368
00:27:52.800 --> 00:27:53.740
But it was taken!

369
00:27:56.620 --> 00:28:01.510
Upper Yard is our homeland,
and at the same time,

370
00:28:01.510 --> 00:28:05.790
it also bears great history
that's been obscured by time.

371
00:28:05.790 --> 00:28:08.990
Even though we're now in the sky,

372
00:28:08.990 --> 00:28:13.760
we must not allow the cherished
Light of Shandora to die out!

373
00:28:20.560 --> 00:28:21.690
No way...

374
00:28:23.190 --> 00:28:24.600
Did he beat him?

375
00:28:36.210 --> 00:28:37.820
Robin!

376
00:28:38.290 --> 00:28:39.530
Weird knight!

377
00:28:50.810 --> 00:28:51.830
Don't tell me...

378
00:28:51.830 --> 00:28:55.260
He's restarting his own heart?!

379
00:29:10.900 --> 00:29:14.350
It's not that people fear gods.

380
00:29:19.240 --> 00:29:21.780
Gods are fear.

381
00:29:26.280 --> 00:29:29.050
What the hell... is with this guy?!

382
00:29:31.310 --> 00:29:35.030
Wyper the warrior. Did I not tell you?

383
00:29:35.980 --> 00:29:38.260
You really shouldn't have...

384
00:29:42.310 --> 00:29:44.410
Look what happened.

385
00:29:46.370 --> 00:29:48.580
How pitiful...

386
00:29:49.640 --> 00:29:51.820
Wyper the warrior!

387
00:29:54.290 --> 00:29:55.880
Don't sully my name…

388
00:29:57.660 --> 00:29:59.360
with your filthy mouth!

389
00:30:01.220 --> 00:30:03.200
Eight hundred years ago...

390
00:30:03.900 --> 00:30:10.910
proud Shandian warriors fought
for the fate of this city.

391
00:30:11.480 --> 00:30:14.080
We are their descendants!

392
00:30:15.470 --> 00:30:18.890
One day, our homeland
was suddenly taken from us.

393
00:30:18.890 --> 00:30:23.220
We've carried on the great warrior
Kalgara's regret for 400 years.

394
00:30:23.220 --> 00:30:27.840
We have struggled for generations
just to reach our home.

395
00:30:27.840 --> 00:30:31.560
And I… finally made it!

396
00:30:36.790 --> 00:30:41.990
You are... in my way!

397
00:30:48.050 --> 00:30:51.010
You got me good there, Wyper.

398
00:30:52.420 --> 00:30:56.510
What a cheap trick,
using that seastone.

399
00:30:56.510 --> 00:30:58.600
On top of that,
one shot of a reject dial...

400
00:30:58.600 --> 00:31:02.400
should be suicide for most people.

401
00:31:02.400 --> 00:31:07.820
You shot it twice and can
still get back up… I expected no less.

402
00:31:12.840 --> 00:31:15.650
Unfortunately, you are
severely outmatched.

403
00:31:22.600 --> 00:31:24.900
The drum... became a bird!

404
00:31:28.870 --> 00:31:31.830
30 Million Volts...

405
00:31:31.830 --> 00:31:33.130
Hino!

406
00:31:48.580 --> 00:31:50.890
So this has seastone in it!

407
00:31:52.870 --> 00:31:56.200
You as well, swordsman
from the Blue Sea...?

408
00:31:57.060 --> 00:31:59.110
It's kill or be killed, right?!

409
00:32:01.800 --> 00:32:03.400
Kiten!

410
00:32:11.820 --> 00:32:12.790
Zoro!

411
00:32:27.060 --> 00:32:29.050
I don't believe it...!

412
00:32:29.890 --> 00:32:31.260
Even Zoro!

413
00:32:32.350 --> 00:32:34.470
Everyone was just... taken out!

414
00:32:45.090 --> 00:32:46.440
Why...?

415
00:32:56.000 --> 00:32:57.080
That man...

416
00:32:58.770 --> 00:33:00.610
Even in that state, he still…

417
00:33:02.840 --> 00:33:04.810
He still intends to fight?

418
00:33:07.560 --> 00:33:09.520
Why do you persist?

419
00:33:09.520 --> 00:33:13.390
You're dying either way.
Isn't it easier to just let go?

420
00:33:15.880 --> 00:33:18.060
Four hundred years, you said?

421
00:33:18.480 --> 00:33:23.270
Since you Shandians started your
fight to take back your homeland?

422
00:33:23.270 --> 00:33:27.710
And yet, you are the only
warrior who made it here.

423
00:33:27.710 --> 00:33:31.490
This nation will soon fall
back to the Blue Sea.

424
00:33:31.810 --> 00:33:32.950
God is...

425
00:33:35.290 --> 00:33:38.410
At this point, your struggling
is nothing but a nuisance.

426
00:33:38.700 --> 00:33:41.370
This guy is clearly unstoppable!

427
00:33:41.950 --> 00:33:43.930
So why do you still persist?

428
00:33:47.880 --> 00:33:49.880
For my ancestors!

429
00:33:56.510 --> 00:34:00.300
I expected a slightly
better answer than that.

430
00:34:00.300 --> 00:34:03.400
But to be fair, you probably
aren't even fully conscious.

431
00:34:08.590 --> 00:34:09.630
Wyper...

432
00:34:12.620 --> 00:34:15.290
Wyper, come here.

433
00:34:17.380 --> 00:34:18.080
What is it?

434
00:34:23.050 --> 00:34:26.310
Since you are a descendant
of the great warrior Kalgara,

435
00:34:26.310 --> 00:34:27.920
I need to tell you something.

436
00:34:28.650 --> 00:34:35.000
You see, there's another reason why
he wanted to take back our homeland.

437
00:34:35.000 --> 00:34:37.760
Another... reason?

438
00:34:38.550 --> 00:34:39.780
Indeed.

439
00:34:40.350 --> 00:34:44.740
It is Kalgara's single biggest regret.

440
00:34:45.580 --> 00:34:49.280
Listen. The great
warrior Kalgara had...

441
00:34:49.860 --> 00:34:51.320
El Thor!

442
00:35:16.690 --> 00:35:20.100
It seems you're the only one left.

443
00:35:43.870 --> 00:35:45.190
I...

444
00:35:51.910 --> 00:35:55.090
I… I would like to go with you!

445
00:35:59.740 --> 00:36:02.180
I'll follow you!

446
00:36:02.680 --> 00:36:04.310
To the dream world!

447
00:36:08.830 --> 00:36:10.500
Is that a no...?
